I am an enthusiastic cybersecurity learner who is deeply passionate about technology and constantly motivated to expand my skills in the security field. I enjoy exploring how information flows online, understanding how attackers think, and ethically uncovering publicly available data to strengthen digital safety. My strengths include fast learning, strong curiosity, problem-solving, and the ability to communicate complex ideas clearly.

Guided by values such as the ethical use of technology and protecting personal information, I am dedicated to helping organizations secure their systems and safeguard user data. My interests span social-engineering awareness, ethical hacking, threat detection, and log analysis‚Äîareas where I aim to build strong technical expertise.

As a fresher seeking entry-level opportunities, my professional focus is on contributing to Security Operations Center (SOC) teams and supporting cybersecurity recruiters who are looking for motivated, dedicated, and security-minded individuals. I am committed to continuous learning and to applying my skills to help organizations strengthen their security posture.

## Skills Highlighted

- Strong interest in cybersecurity and ethical hacking  
- Ethical use of technology and protection of personal data (PII)  
- Curiosity-driven research and OSINT-style information gathering  
- Motivation to work in SOC and entry-level security roles  
- Commitment to continuous learning and professional growth
